    "attributes": {
        "action": "Ban unsolicited mail where a \u201cno junk mail\u201d sign is displayed",
        "additional_details": "It would be more cost effective and better for the environment to only deliver to people who wish to receive advertising.\r\n \r\nSome have made requests to the individual companies to stop posting their marketing material, but the companies do not always comply with the request and continue to post their material. No means No, and all companies should respect a persons\u2019 wishes if they have a sign on their letterbox saying \u2018no junk mail\u2019.",
        "background": "We would like the Government to make it illegal to, and impose fines for, posting unsolicited mail through letterboxes that display a \u201cno junk mail\u201d sign. This ban should include all forms of advertising such as leaflets, flyers, magazines, free papers and take away menus.",
